defaultIdentificationdefault default- 
defaultIdentification of people with disabilities is hard enough but identification of people with complex disabilities is even harder. 
default&#xa0;
default4.3.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe census is one way to identify the number of disabled 
defaultpeople in a country and the Washington Group on Disability Statistics
default has been formulating questions over the last ten years or so that many countries include within their census’.  However, social stigma prevents many families bringing forward people wit
defaulth deafblindness for the census.  In addition to this, trainings for staff carrying out the census in complex disabilities are needed in order to facilitate their identification of this group.
default&#xa0;
default4.3.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThis has much wider implications for inclusion and DFID’s work.
default  Issues of shame, embarrassment and fear prevent participation.  How people view deafblindness needs to change. If this doesn’t occur take up rates for any programme or project will never increase/reach target.
